    <text>
        <body>
            <head>102. Memorandum From Secretary of State <persName corresp="recRM4qiy2MVhNDPu"
                    >Vance</persName> to President <persName corresp="reccm3OnsdQpGeNR8"
                    >Carter</persName>
                <note n="1" place="foot" type="source" xml:id="d102fn1">Source: Carter Library,
                    National Security Affairs, Brzezinski Material, Country File, Box 48, Libya:
                    1/77–1/81. Secret; <gloss target="#t_Nodis_1">Nodis</gloss>. Sent to <persName
                        corresp="reccm3OnsdQpGeNR8">Carter</persName> under a July 2 covering
                    memorandum from <persName corresp="rectQC2yY4UhXLeKu">Brzezinski</persName>, who
                    recommended that <persName corresp="reccm3OnsdQpGeNR8">Carter</persName> approve
                    the recommendations.</note>
            </head>
            <opener>
                <dateline rendition="#right">
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1979-06-22"
                        >June 22, 1979</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <list type="subject">
                <head>SUBJECT</head>
                <item>
                    <persName corresp="recIEUqCutc3qMOCv">Newsom</persName> Mission to <placeName
                        corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libya</placeName>
                </item>
            </list>
            <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">Summary</p>
            <p>At your request, <persName corresp="recIEUqCutc3qMOCv">David Newsom</persName>
                visited <placeName corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libya</placeName> on June 16–18 to
                discuss <rs type="compound-subject" corresp="recRtTKQqtxKMBMhV">relations</rs> with
                the U.S. and <placeName corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libyan</placeName> reaction to
                the <orgName corresp="reck3LdeNURzc3wOV">Boeing</orgName> turndown. <persName
                    corresp="recIEUqCutc3qMOCv">Newsom</persName> met with the number two official,
                Major <persName corresp="recU4berhukXjdZ1F">Jallud</persName>, and with the Foreign
                    Minister.<note n="2" place="foot" xml:id="d102fn2">See <ref target="#d101"
                        >Document 101</ref>.</note>
                <persName corresp="recQAFmups6ngiYAU">Qadhafi</persName> was unavailable, apparently
                because of his mother’s death. <persName corresp="recIEUqCutc3qMOCv"
                    >Newsom</persName> found the Libyans willing to talk, but firmly opposed to our
                efforts in the <placeName corresp="recJAi0OpNdSuYev5">Middle East</placeName>,
                unwilling to accept any linkage between what we do bilaterally and their wider
                policies, and angered by our decision not to supply 747 and <rs type="topic"
                    corresp="rec1GiKVfLPrlIGzK">C130</rs> aircraft. You will recall that we stopped
                the 747s after the Libyans used <rs type="topic" corresp="reccFysHaUEN9EX4w"
                    >727s</rs> in their operations in <placeName corresp="recQS1Cl4Z2PTsUiY"
                    >Uganda</placeName>. Following is a summary of <persName
                    corresp="recIEUqCutc3qMOCv">Newsom</persName>’s conclusions on possible
                retaliation against us by <placeName corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libya</placeName>
                and next steps in our <rs type="compound-subject" corresp="recRtTKQqtxKMBMhV"
                    >relations</rs>.</p>
            <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">Setting</p>
            <p>Action against U.S. interests in <placeName corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH"
                    >Libya</placeName> is clearly possible but is not a foregone conclusion.
                    <persName corresp="recIEUqCutc3qMOCv">Newsom</persName>’s reception in Tripoli
                indicates that <placeName corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libya</placeName> wants to
                maintain ties with the U.S., probably to avoid an appearance of dependence on the
                    <placeName corresp="rec7g4kEoiXWBjoX3">Soviets</placeName> and a consequent loss
                of credibility with non-aligned countries. For this reason, <persName
                    corresp="recQAFmups6ngiYAU">Qadhafi</persName> is also courting the Europeans.
                He received Foreign Minister <persName corresp="recWGOCOq1ztthnNz"
                    >Genscher</persName> June 18–20 and hopes to visit Bonn, Rome, Paris and London
                during July. Fear of attack by <placeName corresp="rec8KXzhReLUudAMW"
                    >Egypt</placeName> is another restraining factor, and <persName
                    corresp="recU4berhukXjdZ1F">Jallud</persName> specifically raised the issue of
                U.S. arms supply to <persName corresp="recIigdM8sR9uq1Ip">Sadat</persName>.
                    <persName corresp="recIEUqCutc3qMOCv">Newsom</persName> said it was only prudent
                for <placeName corresp="rec8KXzhReLUudAMW">Egypt</placeName> to look to its
                defenses. He told <persName corresp="recU4berhukXjdZ1F">Jallud</persName> we were
                not encouraging any Egyptian moves against <placeName corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH"
                    >Libya</placeName> and similarly cautioned against any <placeName
                    corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libyan</placeName> moves against <placeName
                    corresp="rec8KXzhReLUudAMW">Egypt</placeName>. On the other hand, the Libyans
                have noted that our policy on commercial exports is tougher on them than on
                    <placeName corresp="reciphf8UBeSlvltl">Iraq</placeName> and other rejectionist
                states. The others, however, are not known to have used <rs type="topic"
                    corresp="rec81deb9Nh3WRhWg">commercial aircraft</rs> for military operations <pb
                    facs="0280" n="259" xml:id="pg_259"/> as in <placeName
                    corresp="recQS1Cl4Z2PTsUiY">Uganda</placeName>. Finally, <placeName
                    corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libyan</placeName> reaction to the 747 decision will
                be affected by a sense of inferiority which <persName corresp="recIEUqCutc3qMOCv"
                    >Newsom</persName> noted in repeated references by <persName
                    corresp="recU4berhukXjdZ1F">Jallud</persName> and others to being the underdog
                and “punished” by U.S. policy.</p>
            <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">Possible <placeName corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH"
                    >Libyan</placeName> Actions</p>
            <p>Direct U.S. interests in <placeName corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libya</placeName>
                consist of 2,500 Americans (principally <rs type="topic" corresp="recSaEMkYGbM62K53"
                    >oil</rs> field personnel), <rs type="topic" corresp="recSaEMkYGbM62K53"
                    >oil</rs> imports of 700,000 bpd (10% of our imported <rs type="topic"
                    corresp="recSaEMkYGbM62K53">oil</rs>), and investments with a current
                replacement value of $2.5 billion. If <placeName corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH"
                    >Libya</placeName> decides to retaliate, a total <rs type="topic"
                    corresp="recVCENpezMj2XgOU">embargo</rs> on <rs type="topic"
                    corresp="recSaEMkYGbM62K53">oil</rs> is probably not feasible unless they cut
                back production which <persName corresp="recQAFmups6ngiYAU">Qadhafi</persName> has
                thus far been reluctant to do. (<placeName corresp="recGkuSlDiu6KVzHj"
                    >Tunisian</placeName> Prime Minister <persName corresp="rec8IOwPGGW4LB0wR"
                    >Nouira</persName> confirmed this assessment to <persName
                    corresp="recIEUqCutc3qMOCv">Newsom</persName>).<note n="3" place="foot"
                    xml:id="d102fn3">See <ref target="#d203">Document 203</ref>.</note> More likely,
                    <placeName corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libya</placeName> would interrupt present
                marketing arrangements with the U.S., placing more <rs type="topic"
                    corresp="recSaEMkYGbM62K53">oil</rs> on the spot market and seeking new
                contracts with Europe. We know that <persName corresp="recQAFmups6ngiYAU"
                    >Qadhafi</persName> broached the possibility of expanded <rs type="topic"
                    corresp="recSaEMkYGbM62K53">oil</rs> markets in <placeName
                    corresp="recUe17pTh04JBoo9">Germany</placeName> with <persName
                    corresp="recWGOCOq1ztthnNz">Genscher</persName> this week. Other gestures, not
                to be excluded, given the emotional element in <placeName
                    corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libyan</placeName> policy, include severing
                diplomatic <rs type="compound-subject" corresp="recRtTKQqtxKMBMhV">relations</rs>,
                offering naval facilities to the <placeName corresp="rec7g4kEoiXWBjoX3"
                    >Soviets</placeName>, or nationalizing less productive U.S. <rs type="topic"
                    corresp="recUatc2rZ79DXSzf">petroleum</rs>-related investments. We will in the
                next month be sending an analyst to <placeName corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH"
                    >Libya</placeName> to develop further what <placeName
                    corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libya</placeName>’s options and general policies may
                be.</p>
            <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">Next Steps</p>
            <p>
                <persName corresp="recIEUqCutc3qMOCv">Newsom</persName> promised the Libyans he
                would report to you on his conversations and provide a further response to them
                after the Asian Summit meetings. The Libyans may also defer possible action until
                after the Muslim month of Ramadan beginning July 25. <persName
                    corresp="recQAFmups6ngiYAU">Qadhafi</persName> has no major speeches scheduled
                until the Tenth Anniversary of the Libyan Revolution on September 1. On my return
                from Asia, I will propose to Foreign Minister <persName corresp="recOGtrQ7no6DYtTO"
                    >Turayki</persName> that we meet for further discussion while he is at the
                General Assembly in September.<note n="4" place="foot" xml:id="d102fn4">See <ref
                        target="#d106">Document 106</ref>.</note> We do, of course, still have the
                option of releasing the 747s, but do not recommend it in the present circumstances.
                We are informing <orgName corresp="reck3LdeNURzc3wOV">Boeing</orgName> that we will
                let the licenses expire and do not intend to reconsider. We have asked <orgName
                    corresp="rec9JONpI4d5UqDCd">Commerce</orgName> to review all four-wheel drive
                vehicles on a case-by-case basis and will carefully review pending orders for jeeps
                without taking immediate decisions. We hope by these actions to buy some time before
                    <placeName corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libya</placeName> takes a decision.</p>
            <pb facs="0281" n="260" xml:id="pg_260"/>
            <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">Recommendation</p>
            <p>That you approve the next steps proposed above.<note n="5" place="foot"
                    xml:id="d102fn5">
                    <persName corresp="reccm3OnsdQpGeNR8">Carter</persName> checked the Approve
                    option and initialed beneath the options.</note>
            </p>
        </body>
    </text>
